CNCP v1 22525
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#12258: Template attributes aren't type checked",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:21:53.932437+00:00",
  "text": "Template attributes aren't type checked\n\n### Vue version\r\n\r\n3.5.12\r\n\r\n### Link to minimal reproduction\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/richardsimko/vue-bug\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Use a `<template>` element in a `v-for`\r\n2. Use an invalid value for `v-bind:key`\r\n\r\n1. Check out the example repo\r\n2. Run `npm run type-check`\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\nType error on the invalid property use in `v-bind:key`\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\nNo error\r\n\r\n### System Info\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Any additional comments?\r\n\r\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: types",
    "language-tools"
  ],
